---

<section id="contribute">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="row">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Contribute</div>
          <h2 class="display">
            The simulator is open. The science is collaborative.
          </h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="lede">
        Bug reports, new physiological models, validation references, and pull
        requests are all welcome on GitHub. We welcome all contributions and
        depending on our availability and the nature of the contribution, we
        will do our best to provide feedback and guidance within a reasonable
        timeframe. We also encourage discussion on the GitHub Discussions page
        for more open-ended topics or proposals that may require community input
        before implementation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="contrib-grid">
      <div class="contrib">
        <span class="tag">Propose</span>
        <h4>Open a discussion</h4>
        <p>
          New physiological models, alternate recruitment laws, or pipeline
          stages should be talked through before a PR.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="contrib">
        <span class="tag">Report</span>
        <h4>File an issue</h4>
        <p>
          Numerical instability, unexpected MUAP shapes, or NEURON compilation
          problems with a minimal reproducer.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="contrib">
        <span class="tag">Build</span>
        <h4>Send a pull request</h4>
        <p>
          Implement, test against the validation suite, and update the docs. CI
          runs the examples on every PR.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
